Items.Name: NOSUCHNICK
Items.Description: Used to indicate the nickname parameter supplied to a command is currently unused.

Items.Name: NOSUCHSERVER
Items.Description: Used to indicate the server name given currently doesn't exist.

Items.Name: NOSUCHCHANNEL
Items.Description: Used to indicate the given channel name is invalid.

Items.Name: CANNOTSENDTOCHAN
Items.Description: Sent to a user who is either (a) not on a channel which is mode +n or (b) not a chanop (or mode +v) on a channel which has mode +m set and is trying to send a PRIVMSG message to that channel.

Items.Name: TOOMANYCHANNELS
Items.Description: Sent to a user when they have joined the maximum number of allowed channels and they try to join another channel.
Remarks: <channel name> :You have joined too many channels

Items.Name: WASNOSUCHNICK
Items.Description: Returned by WHOWAS to indicate there is no history information for that nickname.

Items.Name: TOOMANYTARGETS
Items.Description: Returned to a client which is attempting to send a PRIVMSG/NOTICE using the user@host destination format and for a user@host which has several occurrences.

Items.Name: NOORIGIN
Items.Description: PING or PONG message missing the originator parameter which is required since these commands must work without valid prefixes.

Items.Name: NORECIPIENT
Items.Description: returned by PRIVMSG to indicate that the message wasn't delivered for some reason. ERR_NOTOPLEVEL and ERR_WILDTOPLEVEL are errors that are returned when an invalid use of "PRIVMSG $<server>" or "PRIVMSG #<host>" is attempted.

Items.Name: NOTEXTTOSEND
Items.Description: returned by PRIVMSG to indicate that the message wasn't delivered for some reason. ERR_NOTOPLEVEL and ERR_WILDTOPLEVEL are errors that are returned when an invalid use of "PRIVMSG $<server>" or "PRIVMSG #<host>" is attempted.

Items.Name: NOTOPLEVEL
Items.Description: returned by PRIVMSG to indicate that the message wasn't delivered for some reason. ERR_NOTOPLEVEL and ERR_WILDTOPLEVEL are errors that are returned when an invalid use of "PRIVMSG $<server>" or "PRIVMSG #<host>" is attempted.

Items.Name: WILDTOPLEVEL
Items.Description: returned by PRIVMSG to indicate that the message wasn't delivered for some reason. ERR_NOTOPLEVEL and ERR_WILDTOPLEVEL are errors that are returned when an invalid use of "PRIVMSG $<server>" or "PRIVMSG #<host>" is attempted.

Items.Name: UNKNOWNCOMMAND
Items.Description: Returned to a registered client to indicate that the command sent is unknown by the server.

Items.Name: NOMOTD
Items.Description: Server's MOTD file could not be opened by the server.

Items.Name: NOADMININFO
Items.Description: Returned by a server in response to an ADMIN message when there is an error in finding the appropriate information.

Items.Name: FILEERROR
Items.Description: Generic error message used to report a failed file operation during the processing of a message.

Items.Name: NONICKNAMEGIVEN
Items.Description: Returned when a nickname parameter expected for a command and isn't found.

Items.Name: ERRONEUSNICKNAME
Items.Description: Returned after receiving a NICK message which contains characters which do not fall in the defined set.  See section x.x.x for details on valid nicknames.

Items.Name: NICKNAMEINUSE
Items.Description: Returned when a NICK message is processed that results in an attempt to change to a currently existing nickname.

Items.Name: NICKCOLLISION
Items.Description: Returned by a server to a client when it detects a nickname collision (registered of a NICK that already exists by another server).

Items.Name: USERNOTINCHANNEL
Items.Description: Returned by the server to indicate that the target user of the command is not on the given channel.

Items.Name: NOTONCHANNEL
Items.Description: Returned by the server whenever a client tries to perform a channel effecting command for which the client isn't a member.

Items.Name: USERONCHANNEL
Items.Description: Returned when a client tries to invite a user to a channel they are already on.

Items.Name: NOLOGIN
Items.Description: Returned by the summon after a SUMMON command for a user was unable to be performed since they were not logged in.

Items.Name: SUMMONDISABLED
Items.Description: Returned as a response to the SUMMON command.  Must be returned by any server which does not implement it.

Items.Name: USERSDISABLED
Items.Description: Returned as a response to the USERS command.  Must be returned by any server which does not implement it.

Items.Name: NOTREGISTERED
Items.Description: Returned by the server to indicate that the client must be registered before the server will allow it to be parsed in detail.

Items.Name: NEEDMOREPARAMS
Items.Description: Returned by the server by numerous commands to indicate to the client that it didn't supply enough parameters.

Items.Name: ALREADYREGISTRED
Items.Description: Returned by the server to any link which tries to change part of the registered details (such as password or user details from second USER message).

Items.Name: NOPERMFORHOST
Items.Description: Returned to a client which attempts to register with a server which does not been setup to allow connections from the host the attempted connection is tried.

Items.Name: PASSWDMISMATCH
Items.Description: Returned to indicate a failed attempt at registering a connection for which a password was required and was either not given or incorrect.

Items.Name: YOUREBANNEDCREEP
Items.Description: Returned after an attempt to connect and register yourself with a server which has been setup to explicitly deny connections to you.

Items.Name: NOPRIVILEGES
Items.Description: Any command requiring operator privileges to operate must return this error to indicate the attempt was unsuccessful.
Remarks: :Permission Denied- You're not an IRC operator

Items.Name: CHANOPRIVSNEEDED
Items.Description: Any command requiring 'chanop' privileges (such as MODE messages) must return this error if the client making the attempt is not a chanop on the specified channel.

Items.Name: CANTKILLSERVER
Items.Description: Any attempts to use the KILL command on a server are to be refused and this error returned directly to the client.

Items.Name: NOOPERHOST
Items.Description: If a client sends an OPER message and the server has not been configured to allow connections from the client's host as an operator, this error must be returned.

Items.Name: UMODEUNKNOWNFLAG
Items.Description: Returned by the server to indicate that a MODE message was sent with a nickname parameter and that the a mode flag sent was not recognized.

Items.Name: USERSDONTMATCH
Items.Description: Error sent to any user trying to view or change the user mode for a user other than themselves.
